The people that say we don't believe the New Testament,

00:13:51.740 --> 00:13:53.320
we don't accept the New Testament,

00:13:53.320 --> 00:13:55.820
we're just Old Testament, they're wrong.

00:13:55.820 --> 00:13:57.520
Because we find that the New Testament

00:13:57.520 --> 00:13:59.120
is part of the canon of scripture.

00:13:59.120 --> 00:14:00.640
The New Testament believers that say,

00:14:00.640 --> 00:14:02.080
hey, I'm a New Testament believer,

00:14:02.080 --> 00:14:03.800
I don't need the Old Testament.

00:14:03.800 --> 00:14:05.060
I can just ignore it.

00:14:05.060 --> 00:14:05.900
You're wrong.

00:14:06.980 --> 00:14:09.320
Paul says, I believe all.

00:14:10.200 --> 00:14:11.040
All of what?

00:14:11.040 --> 00:14:15.400
Well, all that is written, notice what he says,

00:14:15.400 --> 00:14:18.300
in the law and in the prophets.

00:14:19.300 --> 00:14:24.220
Does that mean that he believed that God would judge sin?

00:14:24.220 --> 00:14:25.060
Yeah.

00:14:26.100 --> 00:14:29.740
Does it mean that he believed that God had a plan for Israel?

00:14:29.740 --> 00:14:31.140
Yeah.

00:14:31.140 --> 00:14:33.540
Did it mean that he, I mean, you just go through the list.

00:14:33.540 --> 00:14:36.660
I mean, he believed all.

00:14:37.780 --> 00:14:40.600
Now this evening, I ask the question of myself,

00:14:40.600 --> 00:14:42.980
I ask you this evening as well,

00:14:42.980 --> 00:14:45.980
could we really stand and say,

00:14:45.980 --> 00:14:50.620
I believe all things that are written in this book.

00:14:50.620 --> 00:14:53.460
I believe every single verse.

00:14:53.460 --> 00:14:55.300
I believe it.

00:14:55.300 --> 00:14:56.940
By faith, I believe it.

00:14:56.940 --> 00:14:58.540
Could we say that?

00:14:58.540 --> 00:15:00.020
I think some people might say,

00:15:00.020 --> 00:15:01.780
well, I believe most of it.

00:15:03.140 --> 00:15:05.480
Well, which parts don't you believe?

00:15:06.480 --> 00:15:09.540
Which parts are not important?

00:15:09.540 --> 00:15:12.140
I sat at a table probably at this point,

00:15:13.420 --> 00:15:15.580
17 years ago, and I sat at a table

00:15:16.220 --> 00:15:17.060
with a group of people,

00:15:17.060 --> 00:15:20.340
and one of those individuals that was sitting at a table,

00:15:20.340 --> 00:15:22.220
they made this statement in my presence,

00:15:22.220 --> 00:15:24.540
and they said this, well, you know,

00:15:24.540 --> 00:15:25.860
I'm a New Testament believer.

00:15:25.860 --> 00:15:27.580
I don't need the Old Testament.

00:15:27.580 --> 00:15:29.200
It's just not for me.

00:15:30.580 --> 00:15:32.220
And I said, really?

00:15:32.220 --> 00:15:33.720
Really?

00:15:33.720 --> 00:15:36.300
Began to challenge them on that perspective.

00:15:36.300 --> 00:15:38.500
See, tonight, we need the Old Testament.

00:15:38.500 --> 00:15:39.940
The Old Testament and the New Testament.

00:15:39.940 --> 00:15:42.580
See, if you have the new without the old,

00:15:42.580 --> 00:15:45.260
you're lacking, you're wanting, you're saying,

00:15:45.260 --> 00:15:48.180
what is, think about what Hebrews says

00:15:48.180 --> 00:15:49.140
in Hebrews chapter number 10.

00:15:49.140 --> 00:15:51.860
It talks about the law being a shadow

00:15:51.860 --> 00:15:53.660
of good things to come.

00:15:53.660 --> 00:15:55.300
You know, if you read the book of Hebrews

00:15:55.300 --> 00:15:56.300
without the Old Testament,

00:15:56.300 --> 00:15:59.100
you're gonna have no idea what's going on.

00:15:59.100 --> 00:16:00.440
Really, honestly.

00:16:00.440 --> 00:16:01.940
You're not gonna have a clue.

00:16:01.940 --> 00:16:03.460
You start reading Hebrews, and you're like,

00:16:03.460 --> 00:16:04.900
what is going on?

00:16:04.900 --> 00:16:07.740
Because so much of that goes back to the Old Testament

00:16:07.740 --> 00:16:11.580
and shows how that Christ is better, he's superior,

00:16:11.580 --> 00:16:15.820
but it doesn't mean that we are not going to benefit

00:16:15.820 --> 00:16:17.940
from the things that are written in the Old Testament.

00:16:17.940 --> 00:16:20.100
And so Paul says, I believe.

00:16:20.100 --> 00:16:23.760
So he makes, he reveals in this confession, if you will,

00:16:23.760 --> 00:16:26.420
as he's standing on trial, and he's standing there,

00:16:26.420 --> 00:16:28.500
and the accusers, they bring these accusations,

00:16:28.500 --> 00:16:29.820
says, nope, that's not true,

00:16:29.820 --> 00:16:31.540
but let me tell you what's true.

00:16:31.540 --> 00:16:35.880
I worship God after the way which they call heresy,

00:16:35.880 --> 00:16:37.660
and I believe everything.

00:16:37.660 --> 00:16:41.340
I believe all things which are written in the law

00:16:42.100 --> 00:16:43.900
and in the prophets.

00:16:43.900 --> 00:16:46.220
And then he says this, and have hope toward God,

00:16:46.220 --> 00:16:48.220
which they themselves also allow,

00:16:48.220 --> 00:16:51.180
that there shall be a resurrection of the dead,

00:16:51.180 --> 00:16:52.940
both of the just and the unjust.

00:16:52.940 --> 00:16:54.700
See, we believe that this evening.

00:16:54.700 --> 00:16:57.180
I'm looking forward to the resurrection, aren't you?

00:16:57.180 --> 00:17:00.500
I mean, when we understand the truth of what that means,

00:17:00.500 --> 00:17:03.900
Christ is the first fruits, 1 Corinthians 15,

00:17:03.900 --> 00:17:06.180
and what a joy and a blessing that is

00:17:06.180 --> 00:17:08.020
that we understand that.

00:17:08.020 --> 00:17:09.940
We understand that the Bible says

00:17:09.980 --> 00:17:11.060
that Christ shall rise first,

00:17:11.060 --> 00:17:14.340
and we as believers often think about

00:17:14.340 --> 00:17:16.540
the resurrection of the just,

00:17:16.540 --> 00:17:19.340
but understand the resurrection of the unjust as well.

00:17:19.340 --> 00:17:21.420
The Bible says in Revelation chapter number 20

00:17:21.420 --> 00:17:24.060
that the dead, small and great, stood before God.

00:17:25.540 --> 00:17:29.380
And so we find here that Paul says, here's what I believe,

00:17:30.620 --> 00:17:33.340
and what I believe is the result

00:17:33.340 --> 00:17:36.980
of what God has given to us in this book.

00:17:36.980 --> 00:17:38.220
Do you understand this evening

00:17:38.220 --> 00:17:41.420
that Paul did not have the originals?

00:17:41.420 --> 00:17:42.900
He didn't have the originals.

00:17:43.860 --> 00:17:48.740
He had copies of copies of copies of copies, right?

00:17:48.740 --> 00:17:50.100
And so he didn't have the originals,

00:17:50.100 --> 00:17:52.580
but it didn't seem to bother him

00:17:52.580 --> 00:17:53.580
that he didn't have the originals.

00:17:53.580 --> 00:17:54.740
You have some people today running around,

00:17:54.740 --> 00:17:56.060
well, I don't have the originals,

00:17:56.060 --> 00:17:57.860
and so how do I know what?

00:17:57.860 --> 00:18:00.620
Well, because God, who transcends time,

00:18:00.620 --> 00:18:02.300
said he would preserve it,

00:18:03.300 --> 00:18:04.580
and I just believe that he did.

00:18:04.580 --> 00:18:07.060
By the way, that's believing all

00:18:07.060 --> 00:18:08.900
that's written in the law and the prophets

00:18:08.900 --> 00:18:11.780
because God said he would preserve it.

00:18:11.780 --> 00:18:13.540
But then we find in verse number 16,

00:18:13.540 --> 00:18:15.820
a second thought that's revealed to us here.

00:18:15.820 --> 00:18:18.020
We find in verse number 14 and 15

00:18:18.020 --> 00:18:19.460
that Paul reveals what he believes,

00:18:19.460 --> 00:18:22.860
but in verse number 16, Paul reveals how he behaves.

00:18:22.860 --> 00:18:25.460
You've often heard me say

00:18:25.460 --> 00:18:29.540
that what I believe will impact how I behave.

00:18:29.540 --> 00:18:33.179
I've often said that how I behave reveals what I believe,

00:18:33.179 --> 00:18:36.780
but notice the impact that this truth had

00:18:37.500 --> 00:18:38.340
on the apostle Paul's life.

00:18:38.340 --> 00:18:41.300
See, when he said in verse 14 and 15,

00:18:41.300 --> 00:18:42.980
specifically at the end of verse 14,

00:18:42.980 --> 00:18:44.500
that I believe all things

00:18:44.500 --> 00:18:46.540
which are written in the law and the prophets,

00:18:46.540 --> 00:18:49.980
the reality is that what he believed

00:18:49.980 --> 00:18:53.540
had to have an impact on his behavior.

00:18:53.540 --> 00:18:58.540
What you believe tonight has to impact your behavior.

00:18:59.460 --> 00:19:02.220
See, we believe that fire is hot.

00:19:03.220 --> 00:19:08.220
So therefore, we don't stick our hand in fire, right?

00:19:09.700 --> 00:19:10.540
Because we believe.

00:19:10.540 --> 00:19:12.460
Now, have you ever had a little kid

00:19:12.460 --> 00:19:14.980
that doesn't know that fire's hot?

00:19:14.980 --> 00:19:15.820
And what do they want to do?

00:19:15.820 --> 00:19:16.740
They want to go touch it.

00:19:16.740 --> 00:19:18.020
They want to go put their hand in.

00:19:18.020 --> 00:19:18.980
What do you do as a parent?

00:19:18.980 --> 00:19:19.820
No, no, no.

00:19:19.820 --> 00:19:23.980
And eventually, if they are determined enough,

00:19:23.980 --> 00:19:25.619
they touch something that's hot

00:19:25.619 --> 00:19:30.619
and then they learn, as we often say, the hard way, right?

00:19:30.660 --> 00:19:33.460
Listen, I'd rather not have to learn the hard way.

00:19:33.460 --> 00:19:34.940
What about you?

00:19:34.940 --> 00:19:36.140
I don't like learning the hard way.

00:19:36.140 --> 00:19:38.900
Now, the reality is sometimes we all learn the hard way,

00:19:38.900 --> 00:19:42.020
but I'd rather not have to learn the hard way.

00:19:42.020 --> 00:19:43.940
And we find here that Paul says,

00:19:43.940 --> 00:19:47.820
I believe all that's written.

00:19:47.820 --> 00:19:52.820
Therefore, what I believe is gonna impact how I behave.

00:19:52.980 --> 00:19:54.460
So what does he say in verse 16?

00:19:54.460 --> 00:19:59.460
Notice it says, and herein do I exercise myself

00:19:59.460 --> 00:20:01.780
Now, let me just pause there just for a moment

00:20:01.780 --> 00:20:04.780
because this is very interesting how Paul words this.

00:20:04.780 --> 00:20:07.200
When he says, I exercise myself,

00:20:07.200 --> 00:20:10.240
that literally means to labor, to strive.

00:20:10.240 --> 00:20:12.460
We know what exercise is.

00:20:12.460 --> 00:20:17.460
And we find that he's laboring, he's striving for something.

00:20:17.900 --> 00:20:19.220
And what is that something?

00:20:19.220 --> 00:20:21.660
Because of what he believes, he says,

00:20:21.660 --> 00:20:24.100
here's how it's impact how I behave.

00:20:24.100 --> 00:20:27.260
And herein, do I exercise myself,

00:20:27.300 --> 00:20:31.340
notice what he says, to have, how often?

00:20:31.340 --> 00:20:36.340
Always, to have always a conscience

00:20:37.100 --> 00:20:42.100
void of offense toward God and toward men.

00:20:44.660 --> 00:20:49.660
Now, that's a great impact that God's word had

00:20:49.980 --> 00:20:51.620
in Paul's life.

00:20:51.620 --> 00:20:55.260
Paul said, because I believe everything that I've read,

00:20:55.260 --> 00:20:57.700
because I believe that God is a holy God,

00:20:57.700 --> 00:20:59.660
because I believe that God said

00:20:59.660 --> 00:21:02.340
that he would bless those that obey

00:21:02.340 --> 00:21:04.420
and that there would be consequences,

00:21:04.420 --> 00:21:08.060
many times adversity for those that disobey.

00:21:08.060 --> 00:21:09.500
Listen, the Old Testament says

00:21:09.500 --> 00:21:11.500
that the way of the transgressor is hard.

00:21:11.500 --> 00:21:13.780
The Old Testament says that he that covereth his sins

00:21:13.780 --> 00:21:15.100
shall not prosper.

00:21:15.100 --> 00:21:17.980
We find that there are plenty of truths

00:21:17.980 --> 00:21:19.640
that Paul could look to.

00:21:19.640 --> 00:21:22.540
You look at the book of Isaiah, the book of Jeremiah,

00:21:22.540 --> 00:21:24.900
where God is pleading with his people

00:21:24.900 --> 00:21:27.980
because of their sin, because of their wickedness,

00:21:27.980 --> 00:21:31.940
and he says, just come back, just return to me.

00:21:31.940 --> 00:21:34.440
But you would not, you would not hearken,

00:21:34.440 --> 00:21:37.860
you would not listen, and therefore judgment will come.

00:21:37.860 --> 00:21:40.680
Jeremiah is preaching a message of judgment

00:21:40.680 --> 00:21:43.380
on the eve of Babylonian captivity.

00:21:43.380 --> 00:21:45.420
It came to pass, why?

00:21:45.420 --> 00:21:47.260
Because the people would not hear.

00:21:48.380 --> 00:21:50.460
Paul believed all of that.

00:21:50.460 --> 00:21:52.740
And so in believing all of that

00:21:52.740 --> 00:21:55.460
and understanding what God has revealed

00:21:55.460 --> 00:21:56.580
in the Old Testament,

00:21:56.580 --> 00:22:00.620
Paul says, here is how that impacts my life,

00:22:00.620 --> 00:22:02.820
here's how that impacts my behavior,

00:22:02.820 --> 00:22:05.720
here's what I do, I exercise myself.

00:22:05.720 --> 00:22:08.700
I am laboring, I am striving, I am working.

00:22:08.700 --> 00:22:11.660
Get the picture in your mind of a workout

00:22:11.660 --> 00:22:15.020
where you're laboring, I mean, you're working hard,

00:22:15.020 --> 00:22:16.560
and Paul says, that's what I'm doing.

00:22:16.560 --> 00:22:20.260
That's the word that he uses to describe

00:22:20.260 --> 00:22:24.780
the impact that his belief has had on his behavior.

00:22:24.780 --> 00:22:29.780
I am laboring, I am exercising myself to do what, Paul?

00:22:30.020 --> 00:22:34.920
To have always, not most times, not some of the times,

00:22:34.920 --> 00:22:39.920
but to have always a conscience void of offense

00:22:41.660 --> 00:22:45.300
toward God and toward men.

00:22:45.300 --> 00:22:47.540
Now, I want you to think about this just for a moment,

00:22:47.540 --> 00:22:49.940
because we see this phraseology

00:22:50.620 --> 00:22:54.140
when we understand that Paul says that he has this desire

00:22:54.140 --> 00:22:57.700
to have a conscience that is void of offense.

00:22:57.700 --> 00:22:59.700
Now, obviously, you've heard some

00:22:59.700 --> 00:23:02.740
that have had this terminology

00:23:02.740 --> 00:23:04.180
where you may say of someone,

00:23:04.180 --> 00:23:06.540
or they've even said of maybe someone else

00:23:06.540 --> 00:23:10.380
or of themselves, that they had a guilty conscience.

00:23:10.380 --> 00:23:11.940
You ever hear that terminology?

00:23:11.940 --> 00:23:14.780
And maybe you've used that terminology at some point.

00:23:14.780 --> 00:23:16.940
Well, Paul says, listen, I wanna have a conscience

00:23:17.180 --> 00:23:21.060
that is void of offense, that there's nothing.

00:23:21.060 --> 00:23:23.180
It reminds me of what the songwriter said

00:23:23.180 --> 00:23:24.180
when the songwriter said,

00:23:24.180 --> 00:23:28.040
nothing between my soul and my Savior.

00:23:28.040 --> 00:23:30.860
Not just a few things between my soul and my Savior.

00:23:30.860 --> 00:23:32.580
No, I want there to be nothing

00:23:32.580 --> 00:23:34.320
between my soul and my Savior.

00:23:34.320 --> 00:23:37.500
I wanna have a conscience that is void of offense.

00:23:37.500 --> 00:23:40.780
And so, Paul says this is what his desire was.

00:23:40.780 --> 00:23:43.880
We've used the terminology in the book of 1 Timothy.

00:23:43.880 --> 00:23:45.100
We've looked at it already

00:23:45.100 --> 00:23:46.800
as we've studied it on Sunday mornings,

00:23:47.660 --> 00:23:50.360
where the Bible talks about having a pure conscience.

00:23:51.800 --> 00:23:53.000
A pure conscience.

00:23:53.000 --> 00:23:55.400
But we find that the Bible also talks about individuals

00:23:55.400 --> 00:23:59.440
that have a seared conscience.

00:23:59.440 --> 00:24:02.860
We find here in chapter 23 in the book of Acts,

00:24:02.860 --> 00:24:04.960
if you go back just a little bit earlier,

00:24:04.960 --> 00:24:06.660
this is when Paul is standing there

00:24:06.660 --> 00:24:08.380
before the religious Jewish leaders,

00:24:08.380 --> 00:24:11.280
the Sanhedrin, that body, and he's standing there,

00:24:11.280 --> 00:24:14.480
and it says in verse number one of chapter 23,

00:24:14.480 --> 00:24:16.760
and Paul earnestly beholding the council said,

00:24:16.760 --> 00:24:20.520
men and brethren, I have lived in all good conscience

00:24:20.520 --> 00:24:23.320
before God until this day.

00:24:23.320 --> 00:24:25.260
Isn't that a great statement that he could make?

00:24:25.260 --> 00:24:29.360
Why is it that Paul could make that statement in chapter 23

00:24:29.360 --> 00:24:31.980
in verse number one as he stands before the Sanhedrin

00:24:31.980 --> 00:24:35.400
that he can say I have lived in all good conscience

00:24:35.400 --> 00:24:36.980
before God until this day?

00:24:36.980 --> 00:24:38.920
Well, he gives further revelation

00:24:38.920 --> 00:24:40.120
when he stands before Felix

00:24:40.120 --> 00:24:42.540
because he was exercising himself

00:24:42.540 --> 00:24:46.700
to have always a conscience void of offense toward God.

00:24:46.700 --> 00:24:51.700
So therefore, even though the trial before the Sanhedrin

00:24:51.740 --> 00:24:55.620
took place prior to the trial before Felix,

00:24:55.620 --> 00:24:58.520
if we're to look at it in a chronological order,

00:24:58.520 --> 00:25:00.900
the truth of verse number 16 was not something

00:25:00.900 --> 00:25:03.060
that just came up when he was standing before Felix.

00:25:03.060 --> 00:25:05.340
No, this was how Paul lived his life.

00:25:06.340 --> 00:25:09.780
He lived daily, he exercised himself

00:25:09.780 --> 00:25:13.300
to have always a conscience that was void of offense

00:25:13.300 --> 00:25:18.300
toward God, but also toward men, toward men.

00:25:20.500 --> 00:25:25.500
And we find here that as Paul is revealing in verse 16,

00:25:26.820 --> 00:25:31.820
this great truth to us, we have to acknowledge this evening

00:25:32.260 --> 00:25:37.140
that this is the result of what he believed to be true

00:25:37.140 --> 00:25:38.300
of God's word.

00:25:39.220 --> 00:25:42.380
And so when we come to the Bible,

00:25:42.380 --> 00:25:44.300
when we look at the scripture,

00:25:44.300 --> 00:25:46.540
when we've studied for these last six months,

00:25:46.540 --> 00:25:48.980
these 27 verses of scripture,

00:25:48.980 --> 00:25:51.100
and we've studied through those again,

00:25:51.100 --> 00:25:53.260
they're not just a list of suggestions.

00:25:53.260 --> 00:25:56.020
They're not just a, hey, if you like it, take it,

00:25:56.020 --> 00:25:57.380
add this, add that.

00:25:57.380 --> 00:25:59.340
No, we talked about on Sunday morning

00:25:59.340 --> 00:26:02.100
the importance of a biblical worldview,

00:26:02.100 --> 00:26:05.860
not syncretism, not taking some from Christianity

00:26:05.860 --> 00:26:07.180
and some from somewhere else.

00:26:07.180 --> 00:26:10.740
No, here's what God said in his word,

00:26:10.740 --> 00:26:12.420
and I'm gonna believe all of it,

00:26:13.380 --> 00:26:16.460
the total, the totality of scripture.

00:26:16.460 --> 00:26:21.300
This evening, it will impact how we behave.

00:26:21.300 --> 00:26:25.820
It absolutely will have an impact on how we behave.

00:26:26.660 --> 00:26:30.860
Our behavior, again, the flip side of the coin,

00:26:30.860 --> 00:26:34.100
will reveal what we really believe.

00:26:34.100 --> 00:26:36.660
See, if Paul was running around

00:26:36.660 --> 00:26:40.580
doing some of what he was accused of in verses five and six,

00:26:42.140 --> 00:26:45.340
could he truly say that he believed all things

00:26:45.340 --> 00:26:48.500
that were written in the law and in the prophets?

00:26:49.900 --> 00:26:53.540
Is it the case that there are some today

00:26:53.540 --> 00:26:58.540
that their behavior really does not align with their belief

00:26:58.580 --> 00:27:01.540
or what they claim to believe?

00:27:01.540 --> 00:27:05.220
See, tonight, the evidence in the life of Paul

00:27:05.220 --> 00:27:09.700
is clear that he truly believed all.

00:27:09.700 --> 00:27:12.740
See, I believe that God is sitting on his throne tonight.

